xt in the classroom. The basic material in the text remains unchanged, the work of the author and Pedro M. Ogo, principal of Rota Elementary and High School, who is a native speaker of the language. As much as possible, the lessons exclude regionalisms, presenting the language as it is heard generally on Guam, Saipan, Rota, and elsewhere throughout the Mariana Islands.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Oceanic & Australian Languages.2bisacsh1 aTopping, D. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package Archive pre 2000z978311056415040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824840709423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824840709.jpg  a978-3-11-056415-0  Hawaii eBook Package Archive pre 2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK